<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="309" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1127,885,1004]" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,262,885,908]" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1952" box="[268,339,885,908]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aidoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[268,339,885,908]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Aidoia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a monotypic genus traditionally placed in the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gyllenhal" authorityYear="1813" box="[915,1018,885,908]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Cassidini">Cassidini</taxonomicName>
. Since 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aidoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nubilosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="309">Aidoia nubilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a strongly transverse head with small eyes situated in front of mouthparts and prolonged ultimate tarsomere with long tarsal claws similar to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chapuis" authorityYear="1875" box="[936,1122,949,972]" pageId="34" pageNumber="308" rank="tribe" tribe="Ischyrosonychini">Ischyrosonychini</taxonomicName>
, I transfer it to the latter tribe.
</paragraph>
